00:49.968 --> 00:53.721
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>History prefers
legends to men.</i>

00:56.558 --> 01:00.270
<i>It prefers nobility
to brutality.</i>

01:01.688 --> 01:06.276
<i>Soaring speeches
to quiet deeds.</i>

01:08.903 --> 01:14.117
<i>History remembers the battle
and forgets the blood.</i>

01:15.952 --> 01:17.996
<i>Whatever history
remembers of me,</i>

01:18.079 --> 01:20.957
<i>if it remembers
anything at all,</i>

01:22.250 --> 01:25.670
<i>it shall only be
a fraction of the truth.</i>

01:26.754 --> 01:29.841
<i>For whatever else I am,
a husband, a lawyer,</i>

01:30.883 --> 01:32.427
<i>a president,</i>

01:33.636 --> 01:36.222
<i>I shall always think
of myself as a man</i>

01:36.306 --> 01:38.641
<i>who struggled
against darkness.</i>

01:43.104 --> 01:46.566
<i>I leave in your trusted
hands, my dear friend Henry,</i>

01:47.442 --> 01:51.321
<i>this record that begins
when I was just a boy.</i>

01:52.905 --> 01:54.282
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING ORDERS)</font>

01:56.868 --> 01:58.411
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Get on down there.
Hurry it up!

01:58.536 --> 01:59.662
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN SHOUTING)</font>

01:59.746 --> 02:02.457
Please, sir, no. There's
been some kind of mistake.

02:02.624 --> 02:04.083
I ain't no slave.

02:04.292 --> 02:06.794
Let them go! Aaron!

02:06.878 --> 02:07.879
Go back inside!

02:08.545 --> 02:09.547
Let them go!

02:10.423 --> 02:11.716
Will!

02:11.924 --> 02:13.343
Quiet!
He's my friend!

02:13.426 --> 02:14.636
Look away, Abraham.

02:14.719 --> 02:15.803
It's not our place.

02:16.429 --> 02:17.513
Look away.

02:20.058 --> 02:21.392
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

02:27.690 --> 02:28.733
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

02:31.027 --> 02:32.111
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

02:33.571 --> 02:34.572
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

02:35.531 --> 02:36.741
Abraham!

02:38.785 --> 02:39.911
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

02:39.994 --> 02:41.204
<font color="#808080">NANCY:</font>
Thomas, help them!

02:44.916 --> 02:45.958
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

02:46.668 --> 02:48.419
Leave him alone!

02:49.087 --> 02:50.129
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font>
Are you all right?

02:53.633 --> 02:54.676
Did you strike
my friend here?

02:54.759 --> 02:55.927
He was beating my son!

02:56.010 --> 02:57.553
Did you strike him,
Lincoln?

02:57.637 --> 02:59.639
They're not slaves,
and you know it.

02:59.722 --> 03:00.890
I suggest you get
back to your work

03:00.973 --> 03:02.850
before you find yourself
led away in chains.

03:02.975 --> 03:06.104
Until every man is free, we
are all slaves. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

03:06.729 --> 03:08.356
Very well, then.

03:08.439 --> 03:10.942
Since you're all so
concerned with freedom,

03:11.109 --> 03:15.238
you may consider yourself free
from the burden of my employ.

03:15.530 --> 03:17.490
And the debt you've
been working off,

03:18.074 --> 03:19.909
I'd like it paid in
full with interest.

03:20.743 --> 03:22.745
Now, please.

03:28.876 --> 03:32.505
If you get one more penny
from me, Mr. Barts,

03:32.672 --> 03:35.007
it will come with a fist
wrapped around it.

03:40.555 --> 03:41.556
All right, Mr. Lincoln.

03:44.016 --> 03:47.061
There are other ways
to collect a debt.

03:56.779 --> 03:58.156
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR CREAKING)</font>

04:47.371 --> 04:48.956
<font color="#808080">NANCY:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font> No!

04:49.123 --> 04:50.917
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> <i>What's happening
to her, Father?</i>

04:51.083 --> 04:52.794
Please help her!
Please, I beg of you.

04:53.127 --> 04:54.629
You've got to do
something, Father.

04:54.754 --> 04:56.088
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

04:56.214 --> 04:57.298
<font color="#D900D9">(NANCY MUMBLING)</font>

04:57.381 --> 04:58.341
Easy, child.

04:58.424 --> 04:59.717
Look away, Abraham.

05:01.636 --> 05:02.887
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

05:03.095 --> 05:04.806
I've never seen
anything like this.

05:05.181 --> 05:06.432
Strange.

05:07.433 --> 05:09.268
<font color="#808080">NANCY:</font> You promise me.

05:10.061 --> 05:11.437
<font color="#D900D9">(BREATHING HEAVILY)</font>

05:11.938 --> 05:13.731
Let's step outside.

05:18.277 --> 05:20.363
I'm sorry, I don't
know what ails her.

05:23.407 --> 05:24.408
<font color="#808080">NANCY:</font> Abraham.

05:25.743 --> 05:27.370
Come and lie next to me.

05:38.422 --> 05:40.258
I've been writing, Mama.

05:43.886 --> 05:47.348
"Days are swift
as an Indian arrow,"

05:47.515 --> 05:51.018
"flying like
a shooting star."

05:51.185 --> 05:54.856
"The present day is here,"

05:56.023 --> 06:00.570
"and then slides away
in haste,"

06:00.736 --> 06:04.115
"that we can never say
is ours,"

06:04.282 --> 06:07.034
"but only say"

06:07.201 --> 06:09.203
"is passed."

06:14.208 --> 06:15.459
Mother?

06:15.543 --> 06:16.878
<font color="#D900D9">(TREMBLING)</font>

06:17.295 --> 06:18.796
Mother?

06:25.469 --> 06:28.931
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Mama once told me that
I hadn't cried when I was born.</i>

06:29.473 --> 06:32.059
<i>That I'd simply
opened my eyes,</i>

06:32.226 --> 06:35.938
<i>looked at her smiling
face, and smiled back.</i>

06:37.648 --> 06:39.483
<i>My light was gone.</i>

06:39.942 --> 06:42.486
I don't know how he did it...
Abraham,

06:42.653 --> 06:45.114
you promise me...

06:46.490 --> 06:48.534
You promise me you won't go
and do anything foolish.

06:53.664 --> 06:56.292
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Nine years later, my
father joined her in death.</i>

06:57.627 --> 07:00.004
<i>No longer bound
by my promise,</i>

07:00.171 --> 07:04.091
<i>I tried to fortify the nerve
to pursue my vengeance.</i>

07:10.348 --> 07:11.599
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font>
Haven't you had enough?

07:14.852 --> 07:17.939
A boy only gets this drunk
when he wants to kiss a girl

07:18.105 --> 07:19.523
or kill a man.

07:36.374 --> 07:38.084
<font color="#808080">BARTS:</font>
Adam, Adam, let me explain.

07:38.167 --> 07:39.669
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Last one, Barts.

07:40.044 --> 07:42.880
I'm not coming up here to clean
up your messes any more.

07:43.047 --> 07:45.549
<font color="#808080">BARTS:</font> Yes, sir.
I promise.

07:47.009 --> 07:48.636
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

07:49.553 --> 07:52.723
Every so often, I think about what
it would be like to be in the South.

07:53.432 --> 07:55.726
So, where's Henry?

07:55.810 --> 07:57.353
Yes, sir. We've been
looking all over, sir.

07:57.436 --> 07:58.813
Searching high and low.

07:58.896 --> 08:00.356
Low is more likely.

08:00.898 --> 08:03.067
Just find him, Barts.

08:03.234 --> 08:06.946
Oh, and send
a fresh crop south.

08:07.113 --> 08:09.448
We have a lot of
mouths to feed.

08:09.782 --> 08:10.866
Yes, sir.

08:24.755 --> 08:27.049
"Yes, sir, no, sir.
High, sir, low, sir."

08:46.444 --> 08:47.445
For my mother.

08:51.991 --> 08:53.617
<font color="#D900D9">(BARTS LAUGHING)</font>

08:54.785 --> 08:56.245
That was unlucky.

08:56.328 --> 08:58.539
Might have put me
out of my misery.

08:59.457 --> 09:01.208
Where the hell
are you running to?

09:01.292 --> 09:02.668
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

09:03.836 --> 09:05.671
Don't much like
chasing chickens.

09:06.464 --> 09:08.049
Little boy,
all grown up.

09:08.132 --> 09:10.509
Come to avenge
his dear momma.

09:12.595 --> 09:15.014
There are two kinds
of men, Mr. Lincoln.

09:15.097 --> 09:17.349
Those that have the guts
to pull the trigger

09:17.933 --> 09:19.769
and those who do not.

09:20.936 --> 09:23.189
Powder, patch, ball.

09:23.272 --> 09:24.482
Don't mess it up.

09:26.192 --> 09:28.235
You weren't asleep
that night.

09:28.319 --> 09:29.320
Were you?

09:29.528 --> 09:30.571
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

09:32.990 --> 09:36.160
Oh! You dropped the ball,
Mr. Lincoln. <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

09:39.163 --> 09:42.458
Your mama's blood
was sickening sweet.

09:42.666 --> 09:44.502
I hope yours
tastes better!

09:53.928 --> 09:54.970
<font color="#D900D9">(EXHALES)</font>

10:36.762 --> 10:37.805
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

10:39.890 --> 10:40.933
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLING)</font>

10:48.315 --> 10:49.525
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

10:54.572 --> 10:55.698
<font color="#D900D9">(BARTS YELLING)</font>

11:06.458 --> 11:07.459
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

11:18.679 --> 11:19.763
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

11:23.100 --> 11:24.685
<font color="#D900D9">(FAINT SCREAMING)</font>

11:33.277 --> 11:34.320
<font color="#D900D9">(CLATTERING)</font>

11:48.792 --> 11:50.461
<font color="#D900D9">(WOMAN SCREAMING)</font>

12:00.512 --> 12:01.597
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN GRUNTS)</font>

12:08.812 --> 12:09.855
<font color="#D900D9">(WOMAN SCREAMS)</font>

12:10.189 --> 12:11.273
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN GRUNTING)</font>

12:17.196 --> 12:18.239
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

12:21.825 --> 12:24.036
Might I suggest
that we begin by

12:24.828 --> 12:25.871
closing the door?

12:26.330 --> 12:27.706
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font>
Yeah, I'm sorry.

12:30.292 --> 12:31.835
I didn't see anything!

12:41.845 --> 12:43.347
Should we dive right in?

12:44.306 --> 12:47.059
Or are you finding Gabrielle's
egress too distracting?

12:49.019 --> 12:50.896
I'm sorry, sir,
but who are you?

12:51.063 --> 12:53.357
Who I am is
Henry Sturges.

12:53.857 --> 12:55.859
And where you are
is my home.

12:56.277 --> 12:57.945
And what happened...

12:59.196 --> 13:00.864
I saved your life

13:01.031 --> 13:03.993
during your rather pathetic
attempt at taking another's.

13:04.159 --> 13:05.577
What were you
doing there, and

13:05.995 --> 13:07.579
how did you know
I would try to kill Barts?

13:11.208 --> 13:12.251
How?

13:12.334 --> 13:15.879
I watched this boy carry out his
first long-awaited mission.

13:16.547 --> 13:18.299
Drunk, might I add.

13:18.966 --> 13:22.720
And I think, "You have wasted your
time watching this one, Henry."

13:23.220 --> 13:25.639
"He's not
a promising recruit."

13:25.973 --> 13:30.894
"He is just a selfish boy with
his heart set on vengeance."

13:31.353 --> 13:36.400
And I realized, "This boy
is a goddamned idiot!"

13:39.153 --> 13:40.946
"I doubt he even knew
his target was a vampire."

13:42.072 --> 13:43.282
A vampire?

13:43.365 --> 13:46.493
Yes. Immortal,
blood-sucking demons.

13:46.660 --> 13:48.579
Fortunately for you,
Mr. Lincoln,

13:48.746 --> 13:50.706
hunting them is
something of a hobby.

13:50.998 --> 13:53.292
But vampires
are just myths.

13:53.375 --> 13:54.418
Myths don't
beat you senseless

13:54.501 --> 13:57.254
after you've put
a bullet in their brain.

13:57.338 --> 13:58.339
Thank you.

13:58.422 --> 14:00.799
No, Mr. Lincoln,
vampires are real.

14:00.883 --> 14:04.261
They exist in every city
and every state

14:05.054 --> 14:06.263
in the Union.

14:08.265 --> 14:10.768
If what you say is true,
you could help me kill him.

14:10.851 --> 14:12.269
I could pay you
to kill him!

14:12.436 --> 14:14.438
My services
are not for sale.

14:14.605 --> 14:16.357
And the word you are
looking for is "destroy."

14:16.440 --> 14:20.444
It is quite a feat to kill
that which is already dead.

14:24.698 --> 14:25.949
But you don't understand.

14:26.116 --> 14:28.285
My mother was murdered.

14:29.787 --> 14:33.290
And if I teach you how
to murder her murderer,

14:34.124 --> 14:35.959
so what?

14:36.126 --> 14:39.213
How will that
honor her memory?

14:39.380 --> 14:42.883
How will that benefit the next
boy whose mother is taken?

14:43.050 --> 14:45.219
If vengeance is
all you seek,

14:45.469 --> 14:46.970
seek it elsewhere.

14:48.097 --> 14:51.266
Teach me to fight as you do.
Please, I'll do anything you say.

14:51.433 --> 14:54.269
You promise to cast aside
all notions of vengeance

14:54.436 --> 14:56.480
and commit to
the life of a hunter?

14:56.814 --> 14:58.607
You will have
no friends,

14:59.900 --> 15:01.110
no family.

15:01.985 --> 15:04.321
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>I told him
what he wanted to hear,</i>

15:04.488 --> 15:08.075
<i>but all I cared about was killing
the monster that took my mother.</i>

15:08.742 --> 15:10.244
I'm in.

15:13.163 --> 15:14.748
Scottish Highland pistol.

15:14.832 --> 15:17.126
And if one barrel
isn't enough,

15:17.668 --> 15:19.002
seven should do you.

15:20.045 --> 15:21.338
The blunderbuss.

15:21.588 --> 15:23.424
And if you lose
your ball,

15:23.507 --> 15:26.343
you can always stuff your pocket
watch down the end of it.

15:26.718 --> 15:28.011
So, Abe,

15:29.513 --> 15:31.849
which one
takes your fancy?

15:33.016 --> 15:35.936
Actually, I haven't had the best
of luck with shooting irons.

15:37.688 --> 15:38.730
But,

15:40.691 --> 15:42.693
I was a rail splitter.

15:52.578 --> 15:55.205
I would like you to chop this
tree down with a single swing.

15:55.664 --> 15:56.832
That tree?

15:57.166 --> 15:59.293
It's got to be more than a foot across.
That's impossible.

15:59.376 --> 16:00.794
But it isn't a tree.

16:00.878 --> 16:02.588
It's what you hate
most in the world.

16:03.672 --> 16:05.215
So, tell me,
Mr. Lincoln,

16:05.549 --> 16:06.884
what do you hate?

16:08.594 --> 16:10.262
I hate Jack Barts.

16:11.096 --> 16:12.723
Then strike him down.

16:18.854 --> 16:21.064
Well, clearly you don't
hate him that much.

16:22.107 --> 16:23.484
Tell me what you hate.

16:24.610 --> 16:26.445
I hate that my mother
was taken away.

16:28.822 --> 16:29.823
Inadequate.

16:29.907 --> 16:31.742
I hate that
we were afraid.

16:32.910 --> 16:33.911
And?

16:33.994 --> 16:36.622
That my mother and father,
everyone that we knew,

16:36.747 --> 16:37.915
lived in fear.

16:38.373 --> 16:39.374
Pathetic.

16:39.458 --> 16:41.335
I hate that
I was too small.

16:41.418 --> 16:43.337
Too weak.
Yes.

16:43.420 --> 16:45.172
And that you failed...
Yes!

16:45.255 --> 16:46.548
...to protect her.
Yes!

16:46.632 --> 16:49.593
And that you
let her die.

16:49.927 --> 16:51.303
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

16:58.560 --> 17:00.187
Power, Lincoln,

17:00.270 --> 17:01.939
real power,

17:02.105 --> 17:05.442
comes not from hate,
but from truth.

17:12.031 --> 17:13.700
Before you protect others
from darkness,

17:13.784 --> 17:16.787
you must first be able
to protect yourself.

17:18.121 --> 17:21.124
Your enemies have the power to
render themselves invisible.

17:22.084 --> 17:24.795
You must have the ability
to fight blind.

17:24.962 --> 17:27.964
To see, without seeing.

17:29.091 --> 17:30.133
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GRUNTING)</font>

17:30.801 --> 17:32.469
<font color="#D900D9">(BLOWS LANDING)</font>

17:32.553 --> 17:33.554
<font color="#D900D9">(FALLING)</font>

17:34.972 --> 17:36.306
<font color="#D900D9">(COUGHING WEAKLY)</font>

17:41.478 --> 17:42.771
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

17:43.480 --> 17:45.232
Again.

17:59.705 --> 18:00.831
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GRUNTING)</font>

18:09.840 --> 18:11.425
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>In the weeks
that followed,</i>

18:11.508 --> 18:16.179
<i>Henry endeavored to impart a
lifetime of vampire-hunting secrets.</i>

18:16.263 --> 18:18.348
<i>Their ability to
adapt to sunlight.</i>

18:18.432 --> 18:21.268
<i>Their power to render
themselves invisible.</i>

18:21.435 --> 18:25.022
<i>But most of all, he taught
me how to destroy them.</i>

18:25.188 --> 18:27.441
When Judas
betrayed Jesus,

18:27.608 --> 18:30.360
his reward was
30 pieces of silver.

18:30.527 --> 18:34.323
At that moment, those pieces
became a symbol of betraying God.

18:34.489 --> 18:35.866
Of evil.

18:36.033 --> 18:37.743
And silver
became a curse

18:38.118 --> 18:39.620
<i>upon the cursed.</i>

18:41.455 --> 18:44.625
You will never see a vampire
with silver on his person.

18:46.084 --> 18:48.086
Nor see them
reflected in mirrors.

18:48.253 --> 18:51.131
The one thing God placed
beyond the reach of a vampire.

18:51.715 --> 18:53.133
The one thing he
can never possess.

18:53.216 --> 18:54.217
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> Barts.

18:54.301 --> 18:56.053
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font> And the only thing
that renders him powerless.

18:56.136 --> 18:58.138
Henry, Jack Barts!

18:59.556 --> 19:02.142
I give you the targets.
That was our deal.

19:03.018 --> 19:06.355
This is not only
about Jack Barts.

19:07.481 --> 19:10.859
Vadoma,
a ruthless enforcer.

19:11.026 --> 19:12.110
And her brother.

19:12.277 --> 19:14.154
I've seen him before.

19:14.321 --> 19:16.114
I saw him
with Jack Barts.

19:16.281 --> 19:18.575
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font>
They call him Adam.

19:19.701 --> 19:23.455
He, from whom
all others are made.

19:23.830 --> 19:25.874
Vampires have been in the
New World for centuries.

19:27.959 --> 19:31.797
Slaughtering native tribes
and early settlers.

19:31.963 --> 19:35.884
But when the Europeans
arrived with their slaves,

19:36.259 --> 19:39.805
the dead saw a
sinister opportunity.

19:41.014 --> 19:43.684
They built an empire
in the South.

19:43.850 --> 19:46.937
But, in recent years,
they pressed north,

19:47.104 --> 19:49.022
leaving death
in their wake.

19:49.815 --> 19:51.817
It falls to us, Abraham,

19:52.317 --> 19:55.862
the hunters,
to keep the balance.

19:56.071 --> 19:59.491
To ensure that this
remains a nation of men,

20:00.283 --> 20:01.576
and not monsters.

20:02.494 --> 20:04.746
What we do, we do
not for one man,

20:04.913 --> 20:07.457
but for the good
of all mankind.

20:09.710 --> 20:12.629
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Henry sent me off into
the world with a reminder.</i>

20:12.713 --> 20:15.173
<i>No attachments.
No distractions.</i>

20:15.257 --> 20:17.509
<i>No friends or family.</i>

20:17.676 --> 20:19.761
<i>Besides,
who could I trust?</i>

20:20.011 --> 20:21.888
<i>Anyone in this
well-mannered city</i>

20:21.972 --> 20:24.141
<i>might very well
be one of them.</i>

20:24.307 --> 20:25.767
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Son of a bitch!

20:25.851 --> 20:26.852
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

20:31.565 --> 20:35.736
I ever see you here again, I will
have your balls as a coin purse!

20:35.861 --> 20:38.405
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SHOUTING)</font>

20:46.747 --> 20:48.915
Good afternoon, sir. Joshua
Speed at your service.

20:49.082 --> 20:51.585
Abraham. Uh, Lincoln.

20:52.794 --> 20:53.920
I need a bit of help.

20:54.087 --> 20:55.255
All right.

20:55.422 --> 20:58.175
Well, a friend in need,
is a friend of Speed.

20:58.341 --> 20:59.593
What can I get for you?

20:59.760 --> 21:02.429
I don't suppose you know of any
rooms for rent, Mr. Speed?

21:02.929 --> 21:04.723
What sort of room are you
looking for, Mr. Lincoln?

21:04.806 --> 21:05.766
Well, a cheap one,

21:05.849 --> 21:07.350
as I have spent all of
my money on law books

21:07.434 --> 21:08.602
and have none to
spare at the moment.

21:08.685 --> 21:10.103
Now, as you say
you have none,

21:10.187 --> 21:11.980
am I to take your
meaning as "cheap"

21:12.063 --> 21:13.148
or "free of charge"?

21:13.231 --> 21:14.441
Well, on credit.

21:14.691 --> 21:16.735
I don't think you'll find
such a room in Springfield.

21:16.818 --> 21:19.529
People here are strangely
accustomed to being compensated.

21:21.823 --> 21:22.949
Good day.

21:35.170 --> 21:37.547
There is one room,
Mr. Lincoln.

21:37.631 --> 21:41.426
I was recently forced to part ways
with a thieving prick of an associate

21:41.510 --> 21:43.929
and am, therefore,
in need of a replacement.

21:44.346 --> 21:45.430
There's a room upstairs.

21:45.514 --> 21:48.934
It isn't much, but I suppose
it could be had on credit,

21:49.100 --> 21:51.269
if the tenant were willing
to work here in return.

21:53.814 --> 21:55.023
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Dear Henry,</i>

21:55.106 --> 21:58.318
<i>life in Springfield is
less than desirous.</i>

21:58.485 --> 21:59.486
<i>Fear not.</i>

21:59.653 --> 22:03.156
<i>My pittance of a salary doesn't allow
me to deviate from your rules.</i>

22:03.448 --> 22:05.325
<i>No friends, no family.</i>

22:06.159 --> 22:10.330
<i>And certainly, no woman would find
me, and my existence, enticing.</i>

22:10.413 --> 22:11.706
<font color="#D900D9">(BELL CHIMES)</font>

22:17.420 --> 22:18.964
Excuse me.

22:20.507 --> 22:21.675
Excuse me,
I'll be needing these.

22:21.842 --> 22:23.176
Just one second, ma'am.

22:23.885 --> 22:27.597
Well, you needn't call me ma'am,
as if I'm some haggard spinster.

22:28.098 --> 22:29.140
I'm sorry, ma'am.

22:29.266 --> 22:30.308
<font color="#D900D9">(MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

22:30.851 --> 22:32.602
Madam... I mean, miss.

22:34.521 --> 22:37.524
I'm Abraham. Uh, Lincoln.

22:39.401 --> 22:40.777
Mary Todd.

22:41.903 --> 22:42.946
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENING)</font>

22:43.280 --> 22:44.322
Darling.

22:45.323 --> 22:47.242
There you are.

22:47.701 --> 22:50.412
You mustn't flit from store
to store so quickly.

22:50.495 --> 22:53.373
Well, perhaps if you didn't stop to jaw
with every gentleman in Springfield...

22:53.456 --> 22:54.916
I could say
the same for you.

22:57.002 --> 22:59.170
Stephen Douglas.
How do you do?

22:59.254 --> 23:02.257
Abraham... Lincoln.

23:04.426 --> 23:06.970
Are you a voting man, Mr. Lincoln?
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

23:07.220 --> 23:08.388
I... <font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

23:08.555 --> 23:10.807
How do you feel about keeping
slavery out of Illinois?

23:10.891 --> 23:12.183
I'm running for
the legislature.

23:12.267 --> 23:14.185
I'm sure he'd love to hear
your campaign speech,

23:14.269 --> 23:16.062
but Mr. Lincoln was just
about to attend to my list.

23:16.146 --> 23:17.814
<font color="#808080">DOUGLAS:</font>
We were talking, dear.

23:17.898 --> 23:19.816
Slavery, it's
a complicated issue.

23:19.900 --> 23:22.694
I couldn't disagree with
you more, Mr. Douglas.

23:24.487 --> 23:25.739
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

23:28.742 --> 23:30.952
Mr. Douglas, Miss Todd.

23:31.620 --> 23:32.829
You have met my new
associate, Abraham.

23:32.913 --> 23:34.289
A letter came for you.

23:43.798 --> 23:44.966
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font> <i>Dear Abe.</i>

23:45.050 --> 23:47.928
<i>Your prescription awaits
you at the local pharmacy.</i>

23:48.011 --> 23:50.597
<i>Ask for Aaron Stibel,
Junior.</i>

23:50.680 --> 23:52.474
Mr. Lincoln?

23:53.391 --> 23:54.768
I'm so sorry.

23:58.229 --> 23:59.272
Good day of work,
Abraham.

23:59.356 --> 24:00.607
Thank you.

24:10.200 --> 24:12.243
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font>
<i>But don't forget,</i>

24:13.119 --> 24:15.246
<i>always have
a contingency plan.</i>

24:49.698 --> 24:52.075
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font>
Aaron Stibel, Junior?

24:52.242 --> 24:53.243
Yes?

24:59.499 --> 25:00.750
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

25:03.920 --> 25:04.921
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

25:07.382 --> 25:08.425
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

25:09.759 --> 25:11.094
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

25:14.931 --> 25:16.266
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

25:38.580 --> 25:39.581
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

25:39.664 --> 25:42.500
<font color="#808080">PHARMACIST:</font> That's it.
Oh, that's tight.

25:48.882 --> 25:50.341
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

26:00.727 --> 26:03.813
Don't worry. It will only
hurt for a second or two.

26:04.022 --> 26:05.565
Did you eat today?

26:07.817 --> 26:08.860
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLS)</font>

26:13.656 --> 26:14.657
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

26:24.334 --> 26:25.585
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

26:30.340 --> 26:32.050
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

26:34.677 --> 26:36.679
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font>
<i>I had killed a monster.</i>

26:36.846 --> 26:38.681
<i>And I would kill again.</i>

26:40.266 --> 26:44.020
<i>But no amount of death
could make me forget.</i>

26:46.356 --> 26:47.524
<font color="#D900D9">(WHINNIES)</font>

26:58.201 --> 27:00.286
Merciful Christ, Lincoln,
what happened to your face?

27:00.370 --> 27:01.663
Don't worry, I'll still
be able to work.

27:01.746 --> 27:02.747
Work?

27:03.123 --> 27:04.290
To hell with work.

27:04.874 --> 27:06.626
We got invited
to a ball.

27:07.794 --> 27:11.714
It could be your chance to save
Mary Todd from a life of boredom.

27:11.881 --> 27:13.508
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>This suit makes
me look ridiculous.</i>

27:13.591 --> 27:14.717
Nonsense.

27:15.218 --> 27:17.720
But that hat makes you look ridiculous.
Come on.

27:22.392 --> 27:24.727
Come on, come on.
Look, there she is.

27:24.894 --> 27:26.312
Mr. Douglas,
Joshua Speed.

27:26.396 --> 27:28.314
Pleasure to see you.
Mary, you look lovely.

27:28.398 --> 27:29.566
MAN 1: He's still missing.

27:29.649 --> 27:30.650
MAN 2: Who's that?

27:30.733 --> 27:31.818
Aaron Stibel.

27:31.901 --> 27:32.986
Junior or Senior?

27:33.403 --> 27:34.821
Junior.

27:35.446 --> 27:37.407
MAN 2: Who is that man?
MAN 1: I don't know.

27:37.574 --> 27:39.284
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE TALKING
INDISTINCTLY)</font>

27:45.582 --> 27:47.625
Mr. Douglas, you know
Senator Nolan, of course.

27:47.709 --> 27:49.794
Oh, yes, Stephen.
Good to see you.

27:49.919 --> 27:51.171
<font color="#808080">DOUGLAS:</font> Have you heard this news?
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

27:51.254 --> 27:53.339
<font color="#808080">NOLAN:</font> Oh, yes. Yes, we're
looking into it.

27:53.423 --> 27:55.383
Rest assured, this
kind of lawlessness

27:55.466 --> 27:58.094
won't stand in the noble
state of Illinois.

27:58.178 --> 27:59.596
<font color="#D900D9">(SLOW MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

28:09.522 --> 28:10.690
It's called a dance.

28:11.858 --> 28:14.611
If we were meant to sit alone, they
would've called it something else.

28:15.028 --> 28:18.114
Yes, I suppose
they would have.

28:18.698 --> 28:19.782
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

28:20.116 --> 28:21.201
Come, Mr. Lincoln.

28:21.659 --> 28:23.786
You'll ruin the upholstery
if you sit there any longer.

28:28.416 --> 28:30.585
I'm sure you're a very
nice man, Mr. Lincoln,

28:30.668 --> 28:32.795
but you're a...

28:32.879 --> 28:35.632
A shopkeeper,
in a borrowed suit.

28:35.715 --> 28:38.968
<font color="#808080">MARY:</font> No, it's not a matter of means.
Really, no.

28:39.302 --> 28:41.137
I came to Springfield looking
for someone different.

28:41.221 --> 28:45.350
Someone whose life was a bit
more adventurous, and well...

28:45.642 --> 28:46.893
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

28:46.976 --> 28:48.353
My apologies,
I'm never this...

28:48.436 --> 28:49.395
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> Honest?

28:49.479 --> 28:50.563
Rude.

28:50.647 --> 28:52.398
Miss Todd,
may I speak candidly?

28:52.815 --> 28:54.901
I, too, came here
to better myself.

28:54.984 --> 28:57.070
That's why I've taken
an interest in the law,

28:57.153 --> 29:01.950
and why, if I may be so bold, I
have taken an interest in you.

29:02.325 --> 29:05.119
And as for the adventure
that you seek,

29:05.203 --> 29:08.248
I suspect that few men could ever
hope to provide that for you.

29:08.414 --> 29:11.334
Least of all your fiancÃ©,
Stephen Douglas.

29:11.668 --> 29:15.421
Mr. Lincoln, you are
full of surprises.

29:16.506 --> 29:19.384
Miss Todd,
you have no idea.

29:23.429 --> 29:24.514
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font> <i>Dear Abraham.</i>

29:24.847 --> 29:27.267
<i>I've made a deposit at the local bank.</i>
<font color="#D900D9">(COUGHING)</font>

29:27.350 --> 29:31.104
<i>Be careful, it can
quickly disappear.</i>

29:31.688 --> 29:32.772
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

29:40.613 --> 29:42.031
<font color="#D900D9">(CLATTERING)</font>

29:56.713 --> 29:57.714
<font color="#D900D9">(COUGHS)</font>

30:07.557 --> 30:10.393
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Henry, there are more
than I ever thought possible.</i>

30:10.601 --> 30:13.813
<i>Pharmacists,
Innkeepers, pastors.</i>

30:13.980 --> 30:17.400
<i>It's more than
a man can bear.</i>

30:20.570 --> 30:21.612
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

30:23.573 --> 30:24.574
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLING)</font>

30:27.827 --> 30:28.995
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERING)</font>

30:32.123 --> 30:33.166
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

30:37.837 --> 30:38.880
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

30:39.422 --> 30:41.424
Well, I see I'm such
interesting company.

30:41.507 --> 30:42.508
I'm sorry.

30:43.926 --> 30:47.597
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>
I've been working nights.

30:48.431 --> 30:51.059
Really? Is that true?

30:52.685 --> 30:54.937
Do you really want to
know the truth, Mary?

30:59.650 --> 31:01.486
Each and every night,

31:02.487 --> 31:04.280
I go out

31:06.824 --> 31:09.243
hunting vampires.

31:16.667 --> 31:20.421
Well, how do you
hunt these vampires?

31:21.130 --> 31:22.882
With an ax.

31:23.341 --> 31:27.220
A special silver ax,
of course.

31:27.303 --> 31:28.513
Of course.

31:29.472 --> 31:31.808
And how many would you
reckon you've killed?

31:32.809 --> 31:35.978
Five. No, six.

31:37.021 --> 31:40.483
I have killed
six vampires.

31:41.067 --> 31:42.735
My goodness!

31:46.656 --> 31:47.907
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

31:49.575 --> 31:50.660
Abe!

31:53.413 --> 31:57.417
Here I thought you were an honest man.
Really! <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

31:58.668 --> 32:00.169
<font color="#D900D9">(LINCOLN BARKING)</font>

32:01.671 --> 32:03.047
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

32:09.679 --> 32:11.472
Well, I had
a wonderful day, Abe.

32:12.348 --> 32:14.350
As did I, Mary.

32:28.072 --> 32:32.452
Miss Todd, you are a woman of
ravishing resourcefulness.

32:32.618 --> 32:35.913
Mr. Lincoln,
you have no idea.

32:39.125 --> 32:43.254
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font> <i>You will have
no friends, no family.</i>

32:44.464 --> 32:49.427
I, uh, should be going. It's late.

32:53.306 --> 32:55.975
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>How could I bring
her into this world?</i>

32:56.142 --> 32:58.978
<i>A world of demons,
of danger</i>

32:59.145 --> 33:00.605
Good night, then, Lincoln.

33:01.397 --> 33:03.774
Good night, Mary.

33:04.066 --> 33:05.193
Happy hunting.

33:08.738 --> 33:11.574
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>If I truly
cared for her,</i>

33:11.908 --> 33:14.452
<i>the kindest thing
I could do</i>

33:14.911 --> 33:17.163
<i>was walk away.</i>

34:03.793 --> 34:06.420
This hunter is another
of Henry's disciples?

34:07.171 --> 34:08.880
They say
he's a madman.

34:10.675 --> 34:12.635
I can't wait
to meet him.

34:14.594 --> 34:16.013
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

34:22.018 --> 34:24.146
A stock boy,
reading a law book.

34:24.313 --> 34:27.358
What? You studying
to be a lawyer?

34:28.109 --> 34:29.860
As a matter of fact, I am.

34:31.404 --> 34:34.156
All right, what about
a little test?

34:34.322 --> 34:37.118
What's the law for free
slaves in the North?

34:37.284 --> 34:39.704
According to the Fugitive
Slave Act of 1793,

34:39.786 --> 34:41.914
enforcing Article four,
section two,

34:41.998 --> 34:43.623
of the United States
Constitution,

34:43.708 --> 34:46.835
"All runaway slaves must be
returned to their owners."

34:47.003 --> 34:49.463
However, personal
liberty laws state that

34:49.547 --> 34:51.132
"Anyone who is
born free"

34:51.215 --> 34:53.050
"cannot be taken
under this act."

34:53.134 --> 34:54.927
I heard a good
woman once say

34:55.177 --> 34:57.054
"Until all men
are free,"

34:57.221 --> 34:58.806
"we're all slaves."

34:59.181 --> 35:00.266
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

35:01.934 --> 35:03.060
Will?

35:03.477 --> 35:05.688
Will Johnson!

35:06.814 --> 35:08.065
How did you...?
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

35:08.232 --> 35:09.692
I was back home

35:09.859 --> 35:11.277
and heard
you moved here.

35:11.444 --> 35:13.195
Studying to be a lawyer.

35:13.446 --> 35:15.072
That's good. I'm in
need of a good lawyer.

35:15.489 --> 35:16.949
What, are you in
some kind of trouble?

35:17.116 --> 35:19.535
I was freeing slaves down
South on the rail road,

35:19.910 --> 35:21.787
hoping to find my
brother down there.

35:21.871 --> 35:23.831
Some bounty hunters
got after me.

35:23.998 --> 35:26.000
Said I was a runaway.

35:26.167 --> 35:28.044
I need a writ, Abe,

35:28.210 --> 35:29.629
saying I was born free.

35:30.713 --> 35:31.756
You know, Will...

35:31.839 --> 35:33.215
Come on.

35:33.549 --> 35:34.759
Hey.

35:35.259 --> 35:37.011
Speed, this is
Will Johnson.

35:37.094 --> 35:40.056
Will Johnson, my oldest
friend in the world.

35:42.308 --> 35:43.726
The store isn't
going to run itself, Abe.

35:43.809 --> 35:46.812
I'll have him back as soon
as possible, Mr. Speed.

35:46.979 --> 35:48.147
I promise.

35:50.483 --> 35:51.817
You're getting tall, Abe.

35:51.901 --> 35:54.070
Look like you still don't eat
much, either. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

35:54.153 --> 35:55.988
You still afraid
of the dark, too?

35:56.072 --> 35:57.907
Not so much any more.
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SHOUTS)</font>

35:58.074 --> 35:59.909
That's him, Abe.

36:00.785 --> 36:02.328
That's the guy
that's been chasing me.

36:03.162 --> 36:04.830
Gentlemen, gentlemen,
gentlemen,

36:05.122 --> 36:06.582
I'm sure we can work this out.
<font color="#D900D9">(GUN COCKING)</font>

36:06.957 --> 36:09.085
Now I suggest
you walk away, son.

36:09.502 --> 36:12.338
No, sir,
I suggest you do.

36:25.267 --> 36:26.977
<font color="#808080">MARY:</font> I've sent word
to Senator Nolan.

36:27.186 --> 36:28.938
He'll have you out soon.

36:29.105 --> 36:31.440
You're far too kind,
Miss Todd.

36:32.108 --> 36:34.610
And he's far too ugly
to have a woman like you.

36:36.112 --> 36:38.572
I think common-looking people
are the best in the world.

36:39.532 --> 36:41.325
That's why the Lord
makes so many of them.

36:43.327 --> 36:44.745
I just thank God
he was there.

36:45.871 --> 36:48.457
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> But I won't
always be there.

36:48.958 --> 36:49.959
Mary,

36:52.128 --> 36:55.589
what if something was going
on, something terrible,

36:56.465 --> 37:01.804
and you knew that there was no way
on earth that one man could stop it?

37:02.763 --> 37:04.473
What would you do?

37:05.015 --> 37:06.142
Well,

37:09.103 --> 37:11.355
I wouldn't back away from what's
right just because it's hard.

37:13.190 --> 37:16.944
My father used to say, "Plant
your feet and stand firm."

37:18.654 --> 37:21.323
"The only question is
where to put your feet."

37:26.328 --> 37:28.372
We may fail
in this fight.

37:28.539 --> 37:31.500
We may only shatter the
tranquil veil of oppression,

37:31.667 --> 37:33.043
but we must
not be deterred!

37:35.045 --> 37:37.214
For ours is a just
and noble cause.

37:37.715 --> 37:38.924
The cause of freedom.

37:39.008 --> 37:42.052
The very cause upon which
our founding fathers built

37:42.136 --> 37:44.263
this great nation!

37:44.346 --> 37:46.015
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHEERING)</font>

37:48.225 --> 37:50.144
<font color="#D900D9">(TALKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

37:50.853 --> 37:53.981
A voice like that is too strong
to be stuck keeping shop.

37:54.148 --> 37:56.233
I'm actually studying
to be a lawyer.

37:56.317 --> 38:01.030
Ah! Well, Mr. Lincoln, maybe it's
time you thought about politics.

38:03.699 --> 38:05.618
I can connect you
with the right people.

38:05.701 --> 38:07.578
Thank you,
Senator Nolan.

38:10.581 --> 38:11.999
A pleasure young man.
The same.

38:12.082 --> 38:14.084
You're on your way,
Mr. Lincoln.

38:18.214 --> 38:19.840
I sent you to Springfield
to hunt vampires,

38:19.924 --> 38:21.258
not to chase votes.

38:21.425 --> 38:24.512
Lesson one, always have
a contingency plan.

38:24.678 --> 38:25.971
If vampire hunting
doesn't pan out,

38:26.055 --> 38:27.556
I need a career
to fall back on.

38:28.974 --> 38:30.017
I'm being serious.

38:30.100 --> 38:31.936
So am I, Henry.

38:32.102 --> 38:34.271
I have done everything
you've asked of me.

38:34.438 --> 38:36.440
Every letter,
every name,

38:36.607 --> 38:38.442
but never the letter
I wait for,

38:38.526 --> 38:40.361
and never the name
I want most.

38:41.278 --> 38:44.198
When do I get to
kill Jack Barts?

38:51.705 --> 38:53.249
Barts knows about Mary.

38:54.416 --> 38:55.876
It's time.

38:58.045 --> 38:59.088
Abraham,

39:00.464 --> 39:01.590
be careful.

39:08.013 --> 39:09.932
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSES NEIGHING)</font>

39:25.239 --> 39:26.866
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFING)</font>

39:31.287 --> 39:33.956
Abraham-fucking-Linc...

39:34.039 --> 39:35.040
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

39:35.124 --> 39:36.292
Oh! Missed again!

39:37.293 --> 39:39.753
I hope you're better with an
ax than you were with a gun.

39:39.837 --> 39:40.838
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font>

39:49.763 --> 39:51.140
Come on, Lincoln!

39:53.017 --> 39:54.059
<font color="#D900D9">(WHOOPING)</font>

39:56.353 --> 39:59.148
Catch me before
I get to Mary.

40:03.986 --> 40:05.029
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

40:11.660 --> 40:12.786
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

40:19.168 --> 40:20.210
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

40:40.648 --> 40:41.690
<font color="#D900D9">(ROARS)</font>

41:20.688 --> 41:22.856
Catch me if you can, boy!

41:32.574 --> 41:33.575
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

41:48.716 --> 41:49.717
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

42:24.626 --> 42:27.629
There's thousands
of us here.

42:28.422 --> 42:32.468
He won't stop until this
whole country is ours.

42:34.303 --> 42:36.472
And they'll be
coming for you now.

42:36.972 --> 42:41.185
Ask your friend, Henry.

42:48.192 --> 42:49.359
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

42:51.278 --> 42:52.529
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

42:53.781 --> 42:55.783
You shut your mouth,
you stupid whore.

42:55.949 --> 42:58.619
Give me what I need, or
I'll knock your teeth out.

43:08.712 --> 43:09.755
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

43:17.596 --> 43:19.014
<font color="#D900D9">(CHOKING)</font>

43:21.683 --> 43:23.644
You lying son of a bitch.

43:35.656 --> 43:36.824
God damn it!

43:39.034 --> 43:40.327
No, Abe, stop!

43:44.873 --> 43:45.999
You weren't
ready to know.

43:46.083 --> 43:47.876
What, that you
are a vampire?

43:48.210 --> 43:49.920
You are not
the only one

43:50.087 --> 43:53.674
who has lost everything
to vampires.

44:00.556 --> 44:02.850
Just because
the carriage stops,

44:03.892 --> 44:06.937
doesn't mean
we have to.

44:07.563 --> 44:09.106
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN SHOUTING)</font>

44:12.067 --> 44:13.735
Get in the carriage.

44:17.030 --> 44:18.240
Take this.

44:19.283 --> 44:21.577
Run. Just run.

45:23.972 --> 45:25.057
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

45:27.309 --> 45:28.977
<font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font> Henry!

45:29.394 --> 45:31.021
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

45:32.439 --> 45:33.565
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

45:57.756 --> 45:59.174
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

46:14.564 --> 46:16.149
Her soul was pure.

46:18.193 --> 46:19.528
But yours, Henry...

46:23.782 --> 46:24.825
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

46:34.376 --> 46:35.711
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

46:37.212 --> 46:39.047
It's one of
God's little tricks.

46:39.840 --> 46:43.385
Vampires cannot
kill their own kind.

46:43.760 --> 46:46.555
Only the living
can kill the dead.

46:49.099 --> 46:50.726
Welcome to the family.

47:06.033 --> 47:09.578
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font> <i>You can't save the world,
and the ones you love, Lincoln.</i>

47:09.745 --> 47:11.913
You need to
make a choice.

47:15.042 --> 47:16.585
I'm sorry,

47:18.920 --> 47:20.464
but goodbye.

47:22.007 --> 47:23.258
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER CRASHING)</font>

47:58.960 --> 48:00.128
Abe! <font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

48:00.921 --> 48:01.922
Mary!

48:02.005 --> 48:03.465
What on earth
are you doing?

48:03.965 --> 48:05.550
Come on in.

48:05.634 --> 48:07.219
What are you hiding?
Nothing.

48:07.302 --> 48:08.303
Abe?

48:08.887 --> 48:10.806
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font> It's nothing.

48:11.139 --> 48:13.183
Abe, I know
when you're lying.

48:13.475 --> 48:14.559
What are you
hiding from me?

48:14.643 --> 48:15.936
All right.

48:16.103 --> 48:18.063
I didn't want to
tell you this way.

48:18.146 --> 48:20.148
This is not the way
that I planned it.

48:20.315 --> 48:21.775
But if you really
must know,

48:33.453 --> 48:35.455
Mary Todd,

48:37.332 --> 48:40.544
will you make me
the happiest of men?

49:03.024 --> 49:04.025
<font color="#D900D9">(GIGGLES)</font>

49:09.030 --> 49:10.490
And do you, Abraham,

49:10.574 --> 49:13.410
promise to love her,
comfort her,

49:13.577 --> 49:16.705
be honorable and honest
with her in all things,

49:16.872 --> 49:18.707
in sickness
and health,

49:18.874 --> 49:20.917
till death
do you part?

49:23.003 --> 49:24.004
I do.

49:24.379 --> 49:26.590
Then by the power vested
in me by almighty God,

49:26.673 --> 49:28.216
in the great state
of Illinois,

49:28.383 --> 49:29.593
I now pronounce you

49:30.010 --> 49:31.595
man and wife.

49:32.721 --> 49:34.181
You may kiss the bride.

49:37.225 --> 49:38.393
<font color="#D900D9">(APPLAUSE)</font>

49:44.107 --> 49:45.317
Your mother
would be so proud.

49:45.400 --> 49:46.359
Thank you, Will.

49:46.443 --> 49:47.777
I'm happy
you could be here.

49:47.861 --> 49:49.529
You're the only family
I have.

49:50.780 --> 49:52.073
Except for this one.

49:52.699 --> 49:54.201
Congratulations.

49:54.618 --> 49:57.412
May I introduce
Mr. Henry Sturges.

49:57.579 --> 49:59.247
My wife, Mary.

49:59.414 --> 50:01.958
And my dear friend,
Will Johnson.

50:02.125 --> 50:04.586
Heavens, Mr. Sturges, you're
as chilly as the winter wind.

50:04.878 --> 50:05.921
Henry, please.

50:06.087 --> 50:07.964
I'm afraid that's a hazard
of carrying one's own bottle.

50:08.048 --> 50:10.717
Well, you know what they say,
"Cold hands, warm heart."

50:10.800 --> 50:13.178
Yes, but I highly doubt that.
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

50:13.261 --> 50:14.971
Mr. Sturges is
a business associate.

50:15.055 --> 50:16.890
Yes, I thought we could
talk a little business.

50:16.973 --> 50:17.974
Oh, of course.

50:18.225 --> 50:19.434
If you'll excuse me.

50:25.732 --> 50:26.900
What the hell
are you doing here?

50:27.400 --> 50:28.652
Be cautious, Abraham.

50:28.944 --> 50:33.615
One forgets how easily we can
lose the most precious things.

50:34.574 --> 50:37.827
They don't even
know who I am.

51:17.158 --> 51:18.952
Go upriver.

51:19.494 --> 51:24.499
Invite this Mr. Lincoln to
join us at the plantation.

51:25.834 --> 51:28.503
We're going to throw
a ball in his honor.

51:29.170 --> 51:31.006
What makes you think
he'll accept?

51:33.133 --> 51:36.011
I think we can find
a way to tempt him.

51:43.184 --> 51:45.353
It's a good book.
It's good.

51:54.988 --> 51:56.573
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>
Get him!

51:58.825 --> 51:59.826
Abe.

51:59.909 --> 52:01.036
We've got a problem.

52:05.081 --> 52:06.124
They took Will.

52:11.713 --> 52:13.340
What are you
going to do?

52:13.548 --> 52:16.509
I'm going to accept
his invitation.

52:19.220 --> 52:22.223
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Speed deserved to know the
truth of what we were about to face.</i>

52:23.058 --> 52:24.976
<i>I told him everything.</i>

52:25.060 --> 52:28.063
<i>Not knowing if he would
believe me or think me mad.</i>

52:28.563 --> 52:31.316
<i>Not knowing if he would have the
courage to face the monsters</i>

52:31.566 --> 52:33.568
<i>that I had come to know.</i>

52:33.735 --> 52:36.738
You and me, Abraham, together
we can accomplish anything.

53:00.428 --> 53:03.056
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> There are no slaves.
Where are they?

53:04.099 --> 53:06.393
I was just
wondering that.

53:23.702 --> 53:25.787
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)</font>

53:40.009 --> 53:43.513
Something isn't right
about this, Abe.

53:43.596 --> 53:44.597
Yeah.

53:45.265 --> 53:46.766
I don't know
how to dance.

53:46.933 --> 53:50.562
Don't worry,
I'll teach you.

53:51.438 --> 53:53.231
Wait here.

53:54.399 --> 53:55.900
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font>
Ladies and gentlemen,

53:56.484 --> 53:57.861
dinner is served.

54:01.614 --> 54:02.949
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE SCREAMING)</font>

54:56.878 --> 54:57.879
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

55:26.074 --> 55:27.116
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

55:49.097 --> 55:50.515
<font color="#D900D9">(VADOMA SCREECHING)</font>

55:55.937 --> 55:57.856
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Bravo, Mr. Lincoln.

55:58.857 --> 56:01.276
Bravo. You're even
better than I'd heard.

56:02.110 --> 56:04.612
A shame to sacrifice
so many of my best men,

56:04.779 --> 56:06.531
but I needed to know
if you're up to the task.

56:06.614 --> 56:08.199
What do you
want with me?

56:08.283 --> 56:11.202
To see you liberated.

56:11.369 --> 56:14.372
To see you rise up
and destroy your oppressor.

56:14.455 --> 56:16.916
That's interesting advice,
coming from a slave owner.

56:17.000 --> 56:18.418
Men have enslaved
each other

56:18.501 --> 56:21.713
since they invented gods
to forgive them for doing it.

56:21.963 --> 56:25.300
I've seen Jews
build Egypt's glory.

56:28.803 --> 56:30.013
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

56:30.680 --> 56:32.640
<i>Seen Christians</i>

56:33.516 --> 56:36.185
<i>thrown to lions
with my own eyes.</i>

56:37.020 --> 56:41.816
<i>And I've seen Africans sell
their own kind to Europeans.</i>

56:41.983 --> 56:46.905
<i>May I share one of the
revelations of my 5,000 years?</i>

56:47.697 --> 56:50.658
We're all slaves
to something.

56:51.367 --> 56:53.036
I, to eternity.

56:53.202 --> 56:56.372
You, to your convictions. Others,
to the color of their skin.

56:56.456 --> 56:58.333
All I ever wanted

56:58.499 --> 57:02.211
was to see my kind granted
their rightful place.

57:03.379 --> 57:07.467
But there are those of us,
those like your friend Henry,

57:07.842 --> 57:10.178
who enjoy
living in the dark.

57:10.845 --> 57:12.430
And as you're
doubtless aware,

57:12.513 --> 57:15.683
I cannot personally
destroy him, nor he I.

57:17.018 --> 57:20.063
You, Mr. Lincoln,

57:21.648 --> 57:24.943
you could eliminate those
last pockets of resistance,

57:25.026 --> 57:27.862
beginning with
Henry Sturges himself.

57:28.571 --> 57:30.573
All I ask

57:32.158 --> 57:34.869
is for you to
break your chains.

57:36.412 --> 57:37.705
Kill your master.

57:38.331 --> 57:39.666
Be free.

57:39.832 --> 57:42.043
And if I refuse?

57:42.919 --> 57:44.879
Then you go on
your merry way.

57:46.422 --> 57:50.051
After I make you
one of us, and

57:51.386 --> 57:53.596
spoon-feed you
your friend.

57:54.222 --> 57:58.559
Now, a simple "yes"
or "no" will suffice.

57:59.769 --> 58:01.396
Kill Henry,

58:01.688 --> 58:02.855
save your friend.

58:04.107 --> 58:06.734
Feel free to take your
time to decide. Five,

58:08.027 --> 58:09.028
four,

58:09.862 --> 58:11.239
three,

58:11.864 --> 58:12.865
two,

58:14.575 --> 58:15.910
one.

58:16.995 --> 58:18.204
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSES NEIGHING)</font>

58:26.713 --> 58:27.964
<font color="#808080">SPEED:</font> Come on!

58:40.226 --> 58:41.394
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING)</font>

58:42.061 --> 58:43.187
<font color="#D900D9">(WOMAN MIMICKING OWL)</font>

58:45.940 --> 58:46.941
This way.

59:19.390 --> 59:22.643
Miss Tubman, Miss Tubman.
We've been waiting for you.

59:25.063 --> 59:26.064
Come quickly.

59:40.161 --> 59:41.829
<font color="#808080">TUBMAN:</font> People getting
killed every day.

59:42.497 --> 59:43.790
Slaves disappearing.

59:43.998 --> 59:46.292
Some people talk about
monsters and demons.

59:46.626 --> 59:47.835
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN SHOUTING)</font>

59:52.006 --> 59:53.841
Good morning.
Good morning.

59:54.008 --> 59:56.469
How can I assist you
on this beautiful day?

59:56.636 --> 59:57.929
We're looking
for three men.

59:58.012 --> 01:00:00.431
You know, I did see someone
run down that way.

01:00:00.515 --> 01:00:01.641
<font color="#D900D9">(BELL RINGS)</font>

01:00:04.102 --> 01:00:05.812
You're welcome to
come in if you like.

01:00:05.978 --> 01:00:07.647
Our service is
about to begin.

01:00:09.857 --> 01:00:11.192
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Right,
let's keep going.

01:00:17.740 --> 01:00:18.783
<font color="#D900D9">(BABY CRIES)</font>

01:00:21.160 --> 01:00:23.162
I take it y'all
came from up North?

01:00:23.704 --> 01:00:24.705
Yes, ma'am.

01:00:24.872 --> 01:00:27.500
Well, I suggest you get back
there as fast as you can.

01:00:28.334 --> 01:00:29.877
There's a war coming.

01:00:30.461 --> 01:00:32.839
A war for the soul
of the country.

01:00:33.673 --> 01:00:35.800
Going to be all colors
of blood spilled.

01:00:39.345 --> 01:00:42.181
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Our nation was built
on the backs of slaves.</i>

01:00:42.723 --> 01:00:44.433
<i>Their labor,
their blood.</i>

01:00:44.517 --> 01:00:47.395
<i>More blood than you
could possibly imagine.</i>

01:00:47.562 --> 01:00:50.231
I have seen this horror
of the South firsthand.

01:00:50.398 --> 01:00:54.318
<font color="#808080">DOUGLAS:</font> I say the need for peace
outweighs the needs of the blacks.

01:00:54.402 --> 01:00:58.072
I say that if the people of
this great nation want slavery,

01:00:58.239 --> 01:00:59.782
then let them have it.

01:00:59.866 --> 01:01:02.618
The demon of slavery is
tearing our country apart.

01:01:02.869 --> 01:01:06.914
We must stand up. We must
stand strong and fight.

01:01:06.998 --> 01:01:10.835
Fight for the very
soul of our nation.

01:01:10.918 --> 01:01:14.589
Until every man is free,
we are all slaves!

01:01:18.092 --> 01:01:20.845
You cannot take on
slavery, Abraham.

01:01:20.928 --> 01:01:22.680
You cannot take
on the whole South!

01:01:22.763 --> 01:01:25.349
Why, because of Adam?
No.

01:01:25.433 --> 01:01:26.809
Are you afraid of him?

01:01:26.893 --> 01:01:30.813
Because it is the only thing that has
kept them sated for all these years,

01:01:30.897 --> 01:01:33.107
and you take that away,
then no one is safe.

01:01:33.274 --> 01:01:35.443
So you get to choose
who lives and who dies.

01:01:36.527 --> 01:01:37.528
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> A great man
once said,

01:01:37.612 --> 01:01:39.363
"What we do, we do
not for ourselves,"

01:01:39.447 --> 01:01:41.866
"not for one man, but for
the good of all mankind!"

01:01:41.949 --> 01:01:44.035
Not all mankind, Abraham.

01:01:44.118 --> 01:01:45.453
<font color="#808080">MARY:</font> Abe?

01:01:49.248 --> 01:01:50.791
May I have
my husband back?

01:01:51.626 --> 01:01:53.794
He's all yours,
Mrs. Lincoln.

01:01:56.964 --> 01:01:58.799
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Henry only saw
the struggle his way.</i>

01:02:00.301 --> 01:02:02.970
<i>But I began at last
to see it another.</i>

01:02:03.721 --> 01:02:07.642
<i>To see and to feel the even
greater issues at stake.</i>

01:02:08.643 --> 01:02:11.395
<i>So, he and I would
go our separate ways.</i>

01:02:11.812 --> 01:02:13.731
<i>As the Bible says,</i>

01:02:13.898 --> 01:02:17.318
<i>the time had come for me to
put aside childish things.</i>

01:02:17.902 --> 01:02:19.904
<i>I would fight
not with an ax,</i>

01:02:19.987 --> 01:02:23.157
<i>but with words and ideals.</i>

01:02:23.908 --> 01:02:25.034
<i>For a time,</i>

01:02:25.117 --> 01:02:27.495
<i>they proved
a stronger weapon.</i>

01:02:37.296 --> 01:02:40.675
<font color="#808080">PEOPLE:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(CHANTING)</font>
Lincoln! Lincoln! Lincoln!

01:02:47.348 --> 01:02:50.977
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> I appear before you
to take, in your presence,

01:02:51.060 --> 01:02:54.355
the oath prescribed by the
Constitution of the United States

01:02:54.438 --> 01:02:56.440
to be taken by
the president

01:02:56.524 --> 01:03:01.112
before he enters on the
execution of this office.

01:03:01.195 --> 01:03:05.116
The question of slavery is better
settled with a pen than with a sword.

01:03:05.199 --> 01:03:06.200
<font color="#808080">SOLDIER:</font> Fire!

01:03:08.703 --> 01:03:10.413
<font color="#D900D9">(SOLDIERS YELLING)</font>

01:03:24.051 --> 01:03:25.344
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font>
<i>Through twists of fate,</i>

01:03:25.511 --> 01:03:27.638
<i>I found myself at
50 years of age,</i>

01:03:27.722 --> 01:03:32.310
<i>the father of a nation that
was tearing itself apart</i>

01:03:32.476 --> 01:03:34.729
<i>while trying to be
the father to a boy</i>

01:03:34.895 --> 01:03:38.190
<i>not much older than I was
when I lost my mother.</i>

01:03:40.192 --> 01:03:42.236
3,000 more dead.

01:03:48.075 --> 01:03:49.118
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

01:03:56.083 --> 01:03:57.835
When's the last time
you had something to eat?

01:03:57.918 --> 01:03:59.253
I'm not hungry,
thank you.

01:03:59.337 --> 01:04:02.715
You have got to eat, Abe.
You're only human.

01:04:10.848 --> 01:04:12.266
Come along, Willie.

01:04:15.353 --> 01:04:16.520
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> Willie.

01:04:23.944 --> 01:04:25.279
<font color="#808080">WILL:</font> Willie.

01:04:35.623 --> 01:04:39.543
If you do this, there is
no turning back, Abe.

01:04:40.795 --> 01:04:42.213
I know.

01:04:44.048 --> 01:04:47.093
I'm trying to protect
the freedom of a nation.

01:04:48.302 --> 01:04:52.223
If this war is truly a
stand against evil,

01:04:52.306 --> 01:04:54.809
then let it stand
for something.

01:04:56.102 --> 01:04:58.187
If it is a war for
the freedom of man,

01:04:58.270 --> 01:05:01.357
why not give all men
a reason to fight it?

01:05:02.483 --> 01:05:04.693
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> "All persons
held as slaves"

01:05:04.777 --> 01:05:07.738
"within any state or
designated part of a state,"

01:05:07.822 --> 01:05:10.074
"the people whereof
shall be in rebellion:"

01:05:10.157 --> 01:05:12.701
"against the United States
shall be then..."

01:05:12.785 --> 01:05:16.330
"...and henceforward
shall be free."

01:05:20.793 --> 01:05:22.086
<font color="#D900D9">(LOW GROWLING)</font>

01:05:25.506 --> 01:05:26.966
Good morning.

01:05:37.017 --> 01:05:38.352
Precious little one,

01:05:40.396 --> 01:05:41.480
what's your name?

01:05:41.564 --> 01:05:42.565
Willie.

01:05:42.815 --> 01:05:44.859
And your father?
What's his?

01:05:45.025 --> 01:05:46.819
Abraham.

01:05:51.198 --> 01:05:52.199
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

01:05:56.996 --> 01:05:58.038
<font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font>

01:06:06.380 --> 01:06:08.757
<font color="#808080">VADOMA:</font> What a beautiful
silver sword.

01:06:17.183 --> 01:06:20.227
How is our
little soldier faring?

01:06:32.781 --> 01:06:34.783
<font color="#808080">DOCTOR:</font> I've never seen
anything like it.

01:06:35.409 --> 01:06:37.077
I'm sorry.

01:06:38.245 --> 01:06:40.748
I don't know
what ails your boy.

01:06:49.632 --> 01:06:51.091
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERING)</font>

01:07:11.946 --> 01:07:13.864
<font color="#D900D9">(POCKET WATCH TICKING)</font>

01:07:28.963 --> 01:07:30.297
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY)</font>

01:08:09.628 --> 01:08:10.671
Abe.

01:08:12.673 --> 01:08:14.341
Mary's calling for you.

01:08:37.698 --> 01:08:40.283
I'm so sorry, Abraham.

01:08:44.912 --> 01:08:46.206
Why didn't they take me?

01:08:46.540 --> 01:08:48.584
Because they know

01:08:50.336 --> 01:08:52.379
it is a fate much
worse than death.

01:08:53.380 --> 01:08:54.506
Mary

01:08:57.384 --> 01:08:59.261
is inconsolable.

01:09:01.721 --> 01:09:03.807
She says she doesn't want
to go on without him.

01:09:03.890 --> 01:09:05.517
There is a way, Abraham.

01:09:06.727 --> 01:09:09.229
You know that I can
restore the dead.

01:09:10.522 --> 01:09:11.774
<font color="#808080">MARY:</font> Do it.

01:09:17.488 --> 01:09:18.488
Do it.

01:09:18.906 --> 01:09:19.907
Mary...

01:09:20.407 --> 01:09:21.408
Do it!

01:09:23.952 --> 01:09:25.621
Your journal

01:09:27.081 --> 01:09:29.249
the one you always
kept in your coat pocket,

01:09:30.167 --> 01:09:33.337
I know I shouldn't have, Abe, but I
needed to know what you were hiding.

01:09:33.420 --> 01:09:35.005
If what you say
is true,

01:09:35.089 --> 01:09:36.881
I beg you,

01:09:38.759 --> 01:09:40.344
give us our
little boy back.

01:09:41.345 --> 01:09:45.265
Mary, he wouldn't
be our little boy.

01:09:45.724 --> 01:09:48.185
He would be something else,
something terrible.

01:09:48.352 --> 01:09:50.020
Trust me,
you don't want that.

01:09:50.187 --> 01:09:52.231
You're asking me
to trust you?

01:09:53.023 --> 01:09:54.858
After you lied to me
for all these years.

01:09:54.942 --> 01:09:57.528
I did it to protect you,
to protect our family.

01:09:57.611 --> 01:09:58.779
And how did that work out?

01:09:59.697 --> 01:10:01.865
You did this, Abe!

01:10:01.949 --> 01:10:04.201
You did this!
You brought this on him!

01:10:04.284 --> 01:10:05.994
You brought this
on our boy!

01:10:06.620 --> 01:10:08.414
<font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font>

01:10:13.293 --> 01:10:14.628
Let me go to them.

01:10:14.753 --> 01:10:16.672
Make a truce with Adam.

01:10:16.755 --> 01:10:19.508
We must stop this war. Willie's
death is just the beginning.

01:10:19.591 --> 01:10:21.427
Don't you dare
say his name.

01:10:21.593 --> 01:10:23.429
I warned you.

01:10:23.595 --> 01:10:25.013
You didn't heed me.

01:10:25.514 --> 01:10:28.517
How many more boys will have to
die before you listen to me?

01:10:38.777 --> 01:10:40.904
<font color="#808080">SPEED:</font> <i>These boys
are dying in vain.</i>

01:10:40.988 --> 01:10:42.823
We should pull
the troops back.

01:10:44.032 --> 01:10:47.411
Abraham, this war has
cost us countless lives,

01:10:47.494 --> 01:10:49.371
not to mention
millions of dollars.

01:10:49.455 --> 01:10:52.082
I thought we were going to
make this country great,

01:10:52.249 --> 01:10:53.959
not tear it apart.

01:10:54.918 --> 01:10:57.755
This is the only way we can
save the country now, Speed.

01:11:00.382 --> 01:11:02.509
Send in troops.

01:11:09.516 --> 01:11:12.478
Union troops are
flooding onto the field.

01:11:13.353 --> 01:11:15.314
We are now
outnumbered

01:11:15.481 --> 01:11:18.525
and ill-equipped
compared to the North.

01:11:20.110 --> 01:11:21.904
We will support you,

01:11:23.363 --> 01:11:25.574
but you will
need to support us.

01:11:25.908 --> 01:11:27.284
No, thank you.

01:11:28.494 --> 01:11:30.621
Rest assured,
Mr. Davis,

01:11:31.371 --> 01:11:34.291
you'll have as many
of my kind as you need.

01:11:45.803 --> 01:11:47.387
<font color="#D900D9">(SOLDIERS YELLING)</font>

01:11:56.605 --> 01:11:57.815
<font color="#808080">SOLDIER:</font> Fire!

01:12:01.276 --> 01:12:02.653
Fire!

01:12:14.331 --> 01:12:16.166
<font color="#808080">GENERAL:</font> Ready!

01:12:16.667 --> 01:12:17.668
Aim!

01:12:21.421 --> 01:12:22.631
Here they come!

01:12:24.675 --> 01:12:25.759
Fire!

01:12:34.476 --> 01:12:36.103
Why did they
drop their rifles?

01:12:43.026 --> 01:12:44.027
Fire!

01:13:23.817 --> 01:13:26.069
It's the first day
of Gettysburg.

01:13:27.404 --> 01:13:29.197
It's been a disaster.

01:13:29.907 --> 01:13:32.868
I don't think the army
can survive another.

01:13:33.076 --> 01:13:36.788
If the rebels break through,
they'll be here in days.

01:13:40.167 --> 01:13:43.462
The generals think we
should evacuate Washington.

01:13:44.796 --> 01:13:46.632
Run the war
from New York or

01:13:47.674 --> 01:13:49.051
Boston, if need be.

01:13:49.217 --> 01:13:51.136
You have to
win this war.

01:13:53.764 --> 01:13:55.641
If you don't,
then all of it...

01:13:57.643 --> 01:13:59.269
Then our son's death
will have been for nothing.

01:13:59.436 --> 01:14:01.229
How can I win a war

01:14:01.396 --> 01:14:03.565
when I can't even
protect my own family?

01:14:04.107 --> 01:14:07.194
Our men have no way of defending
themselves against this enemy.

01:14:07.361 --> 01:14:12.032
When our bullets are useless, our
bayonets are powerless as this fork!

01:14:12.199 --> 01:14:13.367
This...

01:14:20.332 --> 01:14:21.291
Will!

01:14:21.375 --> 01:14:22.542
Speed!

01:14:22.709 --> 01:14:26.338
This. This is
what we need.

01:14:27.798 --> 01:14:28.882
A fork.

01:14:29.383 --> 01:14:30.509
Silver.

01:14:31.051 --> 01:14:32.678
Okay, okay.

01:14:33.470 --> 01:14:34.888
How much do we need?

01:14:35.722 --> 01:14:37.057
All of it.

01:14:58.870 --> 01:15:00.914
<font color="#808080">VADOMA:</font> And why tell
me this, Mr. Speed?

01:15:01.081 --> 01:15:02.541
Why betray
your friend?

01:15:02.708 --> 01:15:06.253
<font color="#808080">SPEED:</font> He is my friend, but I
love this country even more.

01:15:06.586 --> 01:15:10.924
And he, more than anyone, is responsible
for tearing this nation apart.

01:15:11.550 --> 01:15:13.343
You've done
the right thing.

01:15:16.888 --> 01:15:18.390
I know.

01:15:19.891 --> 01:15:23.020
<font color="#808080">SPEED:</font> <i>32, 33, 34, 35...</i>

01:15:24.187 --> 01:15:26.440
That is a lot
of silver, Abe.

01:15:30.569 --> 01:15:32.779
Now, how are we going
to get all this there?

01:15:53.300 --> 01:15:55.093
I'm sorry, Mary.

01:15:59.139 --> 01:16:02.642
I'm sorry I've kept you
in the dark all these years.

01:16:09.149 --> 01:16:10.275
I need you, Mary.

01:16:19.701 --> 01:16:23.121
I've waited a long time
to hear you say those words.

01:16:38.011 --> 01:16:41.181
I want you to leave
Washington, Mary.

01:16:41.515 --> 01:16:43.683
Miss Tubman,
please have some tea.

01:16:44.810 --> 01:16:47.395
I very much appreciate you
coming to speak with me today.

01:16:47.562 --> 01:16:48.980
Oh, yes.

01:16:49.981 --> 01:16:52.317
Things have not been easy,
what with my...

01:16:52.484 --> 01:16:55.028
The death of my
son and the war.

01:16:56.029 --> 01:16:58.031
I need to get out
of Washington.

01:16:58.198 --> 01:16:59.908
And I need
a lot of help.

01:17:54.254 --> 01:17:55.255
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:17:59.259 --> 01:18:03.096
This war ends tonight.

01:18:07.142 --> 01:18:08.935
And With it,

01:18:10.979 --> 01:18:12.939
our millennia
of darkness.

01:18:13.356 --> 01:18:15.358
We have to do this
on our own.

01:18:15.525 --> 01:18:17.277
No one can know
what's on that train.

01:18:17.444 --> 01:18:20.113
If we don't get those weapons
to those boys at Gettysburg,

01:18:20.280 --> 01:18:21.364
the war is over.

01:18:26.828 --> 01:18:29.539
It's time we had
a nation of our own.

01:18:32.459 --> 01:18:33.793
Come,

01:18:34.502 --> 01:18:36.671
we have a train to catch.

01:18:37.464 --> 01:18:39.966
It's 80 miles from
here to Gettysburg.

01:18:40.133 --> 01:18:43.803
Eighty miles will decide whether
this nation belongs to the living

01:18:44.638 --> 01:18:45.972
or the dead.

01:19:15.752 --> 01:19:17.837
Is everything
all right, Speed?

01:19:19.756 --> 01:19:22.008
I just can't believe you're
still writing in that book.

01:19:22.509 --> 01:19:24.344
It's all in here, Speed.

01:19:24.511 --> 01:19:25.845
The good with the bad.

01:19:48.118 --> 01:19:49.202
What's this?

01:19:49.869 --> 01:19:51.579
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> They're
fleeing the nest.

01:19:52.038 --> 01:19:54.541
Leaving Washington
free for us.

01:20:09.055 --> 01:20:10.390
Look at me.

01:20:12.475 --> 01:20:14.644
I said look at me.

01:20:15.061 --> 01:20:16.229
Leave her.

01:20:16.813 --> 01:20:18.565
Don't want to
miss this train.

01:20:29.784 --> 01:20:30.785
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Let's go.

01:20:48.845 --> 01:20:50.347
Henry, what the hell
are you doing here?

01:20:50.430 --> 01:20:52.724
I just wanted to see how far
your foolishness would take you.

01:20:52.807 --> 01:20:54.017
I don't have
time to argue!

01:20:54.100 --> 01:20:56.227
I didn't come here
to argue with you.

01:20:56.311 --> 01:21:00.106
I came here to tell you that your
dear friend Speed back there

01:21:00.190 --> 01:21:01.441
is a traitor.

01:21:01.649 --> 01:21:02.692
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:21:03.234 --> 01:21:05.695
He betrayed you, Abe.
Speed is leading you...

01:21:05.779 --> 01:21:07.614
You have no idea
what you're talking about.

01:21:12.952 --> 01:21:14.871
That's all
according to plan.

01:21:21.586 --> 01:21:23.129
<font color="#D900D9">(THUDDING)</font>

01:21:57.872 --> 01:21:58.915
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

01:22:03.420 --> 01:22:05.171
You must
get off this train.

01:22:05.255 --> 01:22:07.215
No, you must
get off this train.

01:22:07.298 --> 01:22:09.342
This is not
your war, Henry.

01:22:10.385 --> 01:22:11.428
Ah.

01:22:12.011 --> 01:22:13.138
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLING)</font>

01:22:20.770 --> 01:22:21.813
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

01:22:31.698 --> 01:22:32.740
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

01:22:32.824 --> 01:22:33.867
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

01:22:42.208 --> 01:22:43.209
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

01:22:51.050 --> 01:22:52.218
They're here, Abe.

01:22:52.385 --> 01:22:53.428
A whole heap of them.

01:22:53.845 --> 01:22:55.346
We can't let them
stop this train.

01:22:55.513 --> 01:22:56.848
You go through there
and you're dead.

01:22:57.599 --> 01:22:59.267
Get out now,
it's your last chance.

01:23:03.771 --> 01:23:04.856
Did you load that thing?

01:23:07.400 --> 01:23:09.402
We've got to keep them
away from the locomotive.

01:24:27.689 --> 01:24:28.773
<font color="#D900D9">(ROARS)</font>

01:24:33.069 --> 01:24:34.445
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

01:25:51.689 --> 01:25:52.857
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

01:26:10.667 --> 01:26:12.919
Why don't you let
him go, Lincoln?

01:26:13.086 --> 01:26:15.171
Emancipate yourselves.

01:26:15.338 --> 01:26:16.839
I will never follow you.

01:26:17.006 --> 01:26:19.258
Oh, you don't have
to follow me, Abe.

01:26:19.425 --> 01:26:21.260
I have the train.

01:26:21.427 --> 01:26:22.929
I have the silver.

01:26:23.096 --> 01:26:25.348
Soon I'll have
the whole country.

01:26:25.515 --> 01:26:29.519
I'm going to destroy the
myth of Abraham Lincoln

01:26:29.686 --> 01:26:32.355
so that history will forever
know you not as a man,

01:26:32.939 --> 01:26:34.774
but as a monster!

01:26:35.525 --> 01:26:36.776
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

01:27:13.980 --> 01:27:15.022
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

01:27:38.171 --> 01:27:40.006
Lincoln set us up.

01:27:40.840 --> 01:27:42.216
We've been tricked, Adam.

01:27:43.843 --> 01:27:45.678
There is no silver
on this train.

01:28:05.615 --> 01:28:06.616
Abe!

01:28:15.833 --> 01:28:17.043
<font color="#808080">SPEED:</font> Abe!

01:28:18.836 --> 01:28:20.213
Abe!

01:28:34.185 --> 01:28:35.728
Hello, Speed.

01:28:36.312 --> 01:28:37.605
Where is the silver?

01:28:37.688 --> 01:28:38.689
Silver?

01:28:40.399 --> 01:28:41.359
Should be here.

01:28:41.442 --> 01:28:43.110
Why did you lie to me?

01:28:44.904 --> 01:28:46.656
To get you all
in one place,

01:28:46.823 --> 01:28:48.074
to finish you.

01:28:48.241 --> 01:28:49.450
Speed?

01:28:51.160 --> 01:28:52.912
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font> No!

01:29:53.598 --> 01:29:55.641
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Mr. President!

01:29:56.893 --> 01:29:59.437
There is nowhere
left to run, Lincoln.

01:30:01.230 --> 01:30:02.565
Where is it?

01:30:02.732 --> 01:30:04.233
Where is the silver?

01:30:08.821 --> 01:30:10.031
Right here!

01:30:10.656 --> 01:30:11.991
<font color="#D900D9">(POCKET WATCH TICKING)</font>

01:31:01.123 --> 01:31:02.541
<font color="#D900D9">(HENRY STRAINING)</font>

01:31:44.250 --> 01:31:45.292
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

01:31:53.718 --> 01:31:54.885
Thank you, Henry.

01:31:55.886 --> 01:32:00.975
I suppose some vampires
can be trusted.

01:32:01.809 --> 01:32:04.061
As can some men, Abraham.

01:32:05.730 --> 01:32:07.732
If the train
was a decoy,

01:32:09.066 --> 01:32:10.109
where is the silver?

01:32:11.318 --> 01:32:13.195
This isn't
the only rail road.

01:32:15.698 --> 01:32:18.325
A wise man
once taught me,

01:32:18.492 --> 01:32:21.787
always have
a contingency plan.

01:32:26.375 --> 01:32:27.460
Get me more!

01:32:27.626 --> 01:32:29.795
Bayonets. Bayonets for
Springfield muskets.

01:32:29.879 --> 01:32:31.464
Springfield muskets!

01:32:33.299 --> 01:32:35.885
Five-pounders and grenades are
in the second wagon in the back.

01:32:35.968 --> 01:32:37.303
Go now, go now.

01:32:54.487 --> 01:32:55.821
<font color="#D900D9">(LOW GROWLING)</font>

01:33:18.552 --> 01:33:19.970
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

01:33:34.193 --> 01:33:35.277
Fire!

01:33:43.619 --> 01:33:44.703
<font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font>

01:33:45.371 --> 01:33:48.874
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>Four score
and seven years ago,</i>

01:33:48.999 --> 01:33:52.086
<i>our fathers brought forth
on this continent</i>

01:33:52.253 --> 01:33:56.048
<i>a new nation
conceived in liberty</i>

01:33:56.215 --> 01:33:58.551
<i>and dedicated to
the proposition</i>

01:33:58.717 --> 01:34:02.721
<i>that all men
are created equal.</i>

01:34:03.389 --> 01:34:06.559
<i>Now we are engaged
in a great civil war,</i>

01:34:06.725 --> 01:34:10.104
<i>testing whether that
nation, or any nation</i>

01:34:10.396 --> 01:34:12.773
<i>so conceived and
so dedicated,</i>

01:34:12.857 --> 01:34:15.192
<i>can long endure.</i>

01:34:21.740 --> 01:34:23.367
<i>It is for us,
the living, rather</i>

01:34:23.534 --> 01:34:25.369
<i>to be dedicated here</i>

01:34:25.536 --> 01:34:29.123
to the unfinished work
which they who fought here

01:34:29.290 --> 01:34:31.917
have thus far
so nobly advanced.

01:34:32.710 --> 01:34:35.629
It is rather for us
to be here dedicated

01:34:35.796 --> 01:34:39.049
to the great task
remaining before us

01:34:39.216 --> 01:34:43.304
that from these honored dead we take
increased devotion to that cause

01:34:43.470 --> 01:34:47.308
for which they gave the last
full measure of devotion,

01:34:48.100 --> 01:34:50.811
that we here highly
resolve that these dead

01:34:50.978 --> 01:34:53.939
shall not have
died in vain,

01:34:54.106 --> 01:34:56.942
and that this nation,
under God,

01:34:57.109 --> 01:34:59.820
shall have a new
birth of freedom,

01:34:59.987 --> 01:35:01.155
and that government

01:35:01.322 --> 01:35:06.452
of the people, by the
people, for the people,

01:35:06.952 --> 01:35:10.289
shall not perish
from the earth.

01:35:10.372 --> 01:35:11.790
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEERING)</font>

01:35:22.134 --> 01:35:23.636
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE CLAMORING)</font>

01:35:25.054 --> 01:35:27.056
<i>Our enemies have
made their exodus.</i>

01:35:27.890 --> 01:35:29.225
<i>Some back to Europe,</i>

01:35:29.308 --> 01:35:32.478
<i>some to South America
and the Orient.</i>

01:35:32.728 --> 01:35:37.316
<i>They've seen that America shall
forever be a nation of living men,</i>

01:35:38.234 --> 01:35:41.320
<i>a nation of free men.</i>

01:35:43.072 --> 01:35:45.407
<font color="#808080">STURGES:</font> We make rather
a good team, you and I.

01:35:46.408 --> 01:35:49.411
One can't help but think of all the
good we could do if we had more time.

01:35:50.663 --> 01:35:51.664
Limitless time.

01:35:51.789 --> 01:35:52.748
<font color="#808080">MARY:</font> Lincoln!

01:35:52.831 --> 01:35:57.586
Yes, well,
time waits for no man.

01:35:57.836 --> 01:35:59.755
We're going to be late
for the theater.

01:36:04.009 --> 01:36:06.011
Hold onto this
for me, Henry.

01:36:13.519 --> 01:36:15.020
Mary, darling,

01:36:15.521 --> 01:36:17.648
have you seen my hat?

01:36:17.815 --> 01:36:20.109
It's on your desk
in the office.

01:36:22.486 --> 01:36:24.196
Have you seen my hat?

01:36:24.363 --> 01:36:27.116
Abraham, let me
make you immortal.

01:36:27.283 --> 01:36:28.951
Let us fight through the
ages, side by side.

01:36:29.034 --> 01:36:31.370
Vampires are not the only
things that live forever.

01:36:38.669 --> 01:36:39.920
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:36:50.306 --> 01:36:53.309
<font color="#808080">LINCOLN:</font> <i>History prefers
legends to men.</i>

01:36:54.059 --> 01:36:57.229
<i>It prefers nobility
to brutality.</i>

01:36:57.688 --> 01:37:00.482
<i>Soaring speeches
to quiet deeds.</i>

01:37:01.108 --> 01:37:03.694
<i>History remembers
the battle</i>

